qa.question: What is Paradox AI?
qa.answer: Paradox AI is a modular, quantum‑inspired system that answers questions using trained Q&A, retrieval, and reasoning.

qa.question: What is a qubit?
qa.answer: A qubit is a quantum bit that can exist in superposition until measured.

qa.question: What is superposition?
qa.answer: Superposition is the coexistence of multiple possible states until collapse on observation.

qa.question: What is entanglement?
qa.answer: Entanglement is a strong correlation between quantum systems that persists across distance.

qa.question: What is interference in this AI?
qa.answer: Interference blends and reweights branch probabilities based on phase and similarity to refine outcomes.

qa.question: What is a hyper‑matrix?
qa.answer: A hyper‑matrix stores concept vectors and their superposition branches for fast retrieval and updates.

qa.question: What is a vector embedding?
qa.answer: It is a numeric representation of text where semantic similarity is reflected by geometric closeness.

qa.question: What does “biasing the base vector” mean?
qa.answer: It means mixing the input vector with retrieved answer vectors to steer reasoning towards learned content.

qa.question: What is cosine similarity?
qa.answer: Cosine similarity measures the angle between vectors; 1.0 is identical direction, 0 is orthogonal.

qa.question: What is a clarifying question?
qa.answer: A clarifying question is a follow‑up prompt generated under high uncertainty to narrow the user’s intent.

qa.question: What is retrieval?
qa.answer: Retrieval is the process of searching trained Q&A and selecting the closest matches to the user query.

qa.question: What does ≥ 0.85 similarity do?
qa.answer: It returns the trained answer directly because the match is strong.

qa.question: What does 0.75–0.85 similarity do?
qa.answer: It biases the reasoning vector toward the answer without returning it verbatim.

qa.question: How does feedback work?
qa.answer: Feedback marks Q&A as correct or incorrect, reinforcing or decaying entanglements for future routing.

qa.question: What is Inceptio?
qa.answer: Inceptio models the drive to initiate exploration in the self‑awareness module.

qa.question: What is Equilibria?
qa.answer: Equilibria models balance between competing hypotheses and stabilizes outputs.

qa.question: What is Reflexion?
qa.answer: Reflexion models reflective adaptation after feedback or new evidence.

qa.question: What is Fluxion?
qa.answer: Fluxion models adaptability and willingness to change paths.

qa.question: What does “collapse” do?
qa.answer: Collapse selects a concrete response from a probability distribution informed by emotions and branches.

qa.question: Where is training stored?
qa.answer: Training is stored in data/training.json at the project root.

qa.question: How do I upload CSV training?
qa.answer: Use POST /api/train/upload with a file containing headers “question,answer”.

qa.question: How do I upload Markdown training?
qa.answer: Use POST /api/train/upload with a .md file that has well‑formed Q: and A: blocks.

qa.question: What is the Q: line?
qa.answer: It is a line that starts with “Q:” followed by the question text.

qa.question: What is the A: line?
qa.answer: It is a line that starts with “A:” followed by the answer text.

qa.question: Can I add multiple Q&A in one Markdown?
qa.answer: Yes, repeat Q: then A: blocks; each pair becomes a training item.

qa.question: Can the same question have multiple answers?
qa.answer: Yes; include variants with different contexts or tags in the answer text.

qa.question: How does the hyper‑matrix update on training?
qa.answer: Each Q&A adds a concept (qa:N) using the answer vector and updates entanglements to similar items.

qa.question: What is an entanglement edge?
qa.answer: It is a weighted connection between two QA concepts indicating relatedness.

qa.question: Why do edges decay slightly per query?
qa.answer: To prevent stale over‑connection; active paths strengthen via feedback.

qa.question: How do I see entanglements?
qa.answer: Call GET /api/debug/entanglements to list edges.

qa.question: How do I see emotions?
qa.answer: Call GET /api/debug/emotions for current emotion levels.

qa.question: How do I see the hyper‑matrix shape?
qa.answer: Call GET /api/debug/hyper-matrix to get tensor shape and concept IDs.

qa.question: What is “opt‑in user text training”?
qa.answer: It logs user prompts when the checkbox is enabled to help propose future Q&A.

qa.question: Where do user texts go?
qa.answer: They are appended to user_text in data/training.json with metadata.

qa.question: What is multi‑hop recall?
qa.answer: A blending of several top answer vectors to guide reasoning when matches are moderate.

qa.question: How many answers are blended?
qa.answer: Up to three top answers above a similarity floor are blended with similarity weights.

qa.question: Why return a clarifying prompt?
qa.answer: To reduce uncertainty when retrieval is weak and entropy remains high after reasoning.

qa.question: Can I personalize tone and style?
qa.answer: Yes; set tone (neutral, friendly, formal) and style (concise, detailed).

qa.question: What is the role system?
qa.answer: Users and developers; developers can upload bulk training and manage data.

qa.question: How does login work?
qa.answer: POST /api/auth/login returns a token and role; UI saves them in localStorage.

qa.question: How do I check my session?
qa.answer: GET /api/auth/me?token=... returns authentication and role.

qa.question: How do I logout?
qa.answer: POST /api/auth/logout with the token removes the session server‑side.

qa.question: Can I train on definitions?
qa.answer: Yes; add Q&A with definitions, which will be used in retrieval and biasing.

qa.question: Can I train on procedures?
qa.answer: Yes; write step‑by‑step answers; they are treated like any other text.

qa.question: Can I train on examples?
qa.answer: Yes; answers with examples help retrieval and improve similarity signals.

qa.question: What does “project root data” mean?
qa.answer: The data directory at QuantumGodAI/data where training.json and others persist now.

qa.question: Does the server reinitialize files on restart?
qa.answer: Only if files are missing; existing files are preserved.

qa.question: Why use cosine similarity?
qa.answer: It is scale‑invariant and robust for comparing embeddings.

qa.question: What happens on low similarity?
qa.answer: The system favors reasoning and may ask for clarification rather than guessing.

qa.question: How do I enable bulk upload from the UI?
qa.answer: Use the Developer Dashboard → Bulk Upload (CSV or Markdown).

qa.question: What is the minimum for Markdown upload?
qa.answer: At least one Q: line followed by one A: line; multiple pairs are allowed.

qa.question: Do headers matter in Markdown?
qa.answer: No; plain “Q:” and “A:” are sufficient; “### Q:” and “### A:” are also accepted.

qa.question: Does order matter in Q&A blocks?
qa.answer: Yes; each “Q:” should be followed by its corresponding “A:” block.

qa.question: Can I use punctuation in Q: lines?
qa.answer: Yes; the parser uses the “Q:” prefix and reads the rest of the line.

qa.question: Can answers span multiple lines?
qa.answer: Yes; lines after “A:” are appended until the next “Q:” block or EOF.

qa.question: Is there a size limit?
qa.answer: Keep files moderate; large uploads work but may be slower without an index.

qa.question: How do I correct a bad answer?
qa.answer: Use /api/feedback with qa_id and correct=false; then upload a better variant.

qa.question: Does feedback change retrieval immediately?
qa.answer: It adjusts entanglements and stats; retrieval will gradually favor better items.

qa.question: Can I delete a QA?
qa.answer: Not yet via API; you can edit data/training.json and restart.

qa.question: Can I export the training set?
qa.answer: Yes; copy data/training.json and associated data/ files.

qa.question: Why do I get “added: 0” on upload?
qa.answer: The file had no valid “Q:”/“A:” pairs; check formatting and retry.

qa.question: What is a good format for CSV?
qa.answer: A header “question,answer” and one Q&A per row.

qa.question: How does the system handle ties?
qa.answer: It blends top answers or uses reasoning collapse to arbitrate.

qa.question: Will it learn automatically from usage?
qa.answer: With opt‑in logs and feedback, it adapts by biasing and adjusting entanglements.

qa.question: Can I restrict training to developers?
qa.answer: Yes; only developers should use the upload interface.

qa.question: What is the next upgrade path?
qa.answer: Add FAISS/pgvector indexing for scalable similarity search.

qa.question: Does the system call an external LLM?
qa.answer: Not by default; it uses local retrieval and reasoning. An LLM adapter can be added.

qa.question: What if my domain is specialized?
qa.answer: Upload a tailored Q&A set; retrieval and biasing will align answers with your corpus.

qa.question: Can answers include lists?
qa.answer: Yes; Markdown lists are fine within the A: block.

qa.question: Are HTML tags supported?
qa.answer: They are treated as text; keep answers simple Markdown for consistency.

qa.question: What is the purpose of emotions in output?
qa.answer: Emotions shape smoothing, diversity, and how the collapse balances alternatives.

qa.question: Can I inspect probabilities?
qa.answer: Yes; use the API directly to see probabilities and metadata.

qa.question: Does the clarifying prompt always appear?
qa.answer: Only when uncertainty is high and no strong retrieval match is found.

qa.question: Can I train in multiple languages?
qa.answer: Yes; provide Q&A in the target language; retrieval uses embeddings, not keywords only.

qa.question: What is the role of entanglement among QAs?
qa.answer: It connects related items so future retrieval and biasing can traverse learned structure.

qa.question: Does the system forget?
qa.answer: Entanglements decay slightly per query; rarely used links weaken over time.

qa.question: Can I import multiple Markdown files?
qa.answer: Yes; upload them one after another; they will be appended to training.json.

qa.question: How do I ensure ordering?
qa.answer: Each upload appends; include IDs or timestamps in your own records if needed.

qa.question: Is there a limit on Q&A length?
qa.answer: No strict limit; very long answers may be truncated in UI display but stored fully.

qa.question: How do I view the dataset size?
qa.answer: GET /api/train/qa returns the list; your upload response also shows totals.

qa.question: Are duplicate questions allowed?
qa.answer: Yes; variants are distinguished by answer text and later by stats/feedback.

qa.question: How do I tune selection among variants?
qa.answer: Provide clearer context in the question or use feedback to guide preference.

qa.question: Can I attach tags to answers?
qa.answer: For now include tags textually in the answer like [beginner], [advanced].

qa.question: What happens if I upload the same file twice?
qa.answer: The system will append duplicates; you can deduplicate manually later.

qa.question: Where do I file issues?
qa.answer: Use your project tracker; include sample Q:/A: that failed and the file.

qa.question: How do I back up?
qa.answer: Copy the /data directory; it contains the entire learned state for this system.
